# Caddy ingress for the Swarm bench stack — terminates TLS for jaco.sh (via
# ACME) and reverse-proxies to the web tier, mirroring JACO's Caddy ingress so
# the two stacks are benched over the SAME protocol (HTTPS).
#
# acme_ca is pinned to Let's Encrypt STAGING: this is a throwaway bench and prod
# LE has tight duplicate-cert limits. Staging certs aren't browser-trusted (k6
# runs with insecureSkipTLSVerify), which is fine for a perf measurement.
{
	acme_ca https://acme-staging-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory
	email ops@jaco.sh
}

jaco.sh {
	reverse_proxy web:80
}
